<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,512,683]" pageId="21" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,549,575]" pageId="21" pageNumber="50">Remarks</emphasis>
. The abdomen is lacking in the male, thus it is impossible to identify the species with certainty. Morphologically these specimens are similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Naskrecki, 1992" authorityName="Naskrecki" authorityYear="1992" box="[646,1021,584,611]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Rhachitopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachypterus">
<emphasis box="[646,826,584,610]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="50">R. brachypterus</emphasis>
Naskrecki, 1992
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1210,1333,584,610]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="21" pageNumber="50">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
, the only species of this genus with very short tegmina. Considering the distance of these Angolan specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1316,1436,620,646]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="21" pageNumber="50">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
(ca. 
<quantity box="[199,302,656,683]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="21" pageNumber="50" unit="km" value="1600.0">1600 km</quantity>
), very likely they belong to an undescribed species.
</paragraph>
